summary: An update: After actually finding a link by chance in migraine-induced late night scrolling, I managed to get a ticket for the...
body:
An update: After actually finding a link by chance in migraine-induced late night scrolling, I managed to get a ticket for the screening of the first two episodes of Good Omens.

I had previously cancelled my hotel reservation because I thought I wasn‘t gonna go being sick and just standing in the crowd wasn‘t worth it.

Getting the ticket made me fricking jump, though I have to travel a good day and a half to London I‘m so hyped up for it now.

summary: The floor above him collapsed. With a roar and a gargantuan shrug the building fell in on itself, in a rain of brick and timber...
body:
The floor above him collapsed. With a roar and a gargantuan shrug the building fell in on itself, in a rain of brick and timber and flaming debris.

Outside, the passersby were being herded back by the police, and a fireman was explaining to anyone who would listen, “I couldn’t stop him. He must have been mad. Or drunk. Just ran in. I couldn’t stop him. Mad. Ran straight in. Horrible way to die. Horrible, horrible. Just rain straight in …”

And then Crowley came out of the flames.

The police and the firemen looked at him, saw the expression on his face, and stayed exactly where they were.

 - Neil Gaiman and Terry Pratchett, Good Omens
